Social Media Do’s and Don’ts for College Students:-

✅ Do’s
Use strong and unique passwords for all accounts.
Keep your profiles professional and respectful.
Think carefully before posting any content online.
Verify information before sharing to avoid spreading misinformation.
Use privacy settings to control who can see your posts.
Be polite and respectful in comments and messages.

❌ Don’ts:-

Do not share OTP, passwords, or personal information with anyone.
Avoid posting offensive, abusive, or inappropriate content.
Do not click on suspicious links or unknown messages.
Avoid oversharing personal details like location or financial info.
Do not engage in cyberbullying or online arguments.
Avoid using social media during study or class time excessively.
